Abu Dhabi ’s benchmark  ADX General
Index (ADSMI)  climbed 1.5 percent, the most since May 2010, to 2,402.28
at the 2:00 p.m. close in the emirate, trimming its losses this
year to 12 percent. Qatar’s QE Index fell 0.4 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols follow company names.  Aldar Properties PJSC (ALDAR UH) jumped 9.5 percent, the
most since Dec. 2009, to 92 fils. Abu Dhabi’s government agreed
to buy assets valued at 16.8 billion dirhams ($4.57 billion)
from the real-estate developer.  United Development Co. (UDCD)   slumped 10 percent, the
most since Sept. 2008, to 24.84 riyals after Qatar’s pension
fund offered to buy a stake below its trading value.  To contact the reporter on this story:
